===Etymology===
English translation of {{etyl|ru}} {{term|Санкт-Петербург|tr=Sankt-Peterbúrg|lang=ru}}, from {{etyl|de}} {{term|Sankt|lang=de}} {{term|Peter|Peters|lang=de}}{{term|Burg|burg|Saint Peter's City|lang=de}}, referring to {{w|Saint Peter}} the [[Apostle]] and alluding to its founder [[tsar|Tsar]] {{w|Peter the Great}}.

===Proper noun===
[[Image:Spb collage.JPG|thumb|Saint Petersburg (Санкт-Петербург ''Sankt-Peterburg'')]]
{{en-proper noun|head=[[saint|Saint]] [[Petersburg]]}}

# A major city in [[Russia]], known between 1914 and 1924 as [[Petrograd]] and between 1924 and 1991 as [[Leningrad]], and former capital of Russia (1713-1728, 1732-1918).

